author: COMSOL
description: This example illustrates how to model the deformed geometry as electrodeposition of copper takes place on a cathode surface. Both concentration dependent electrode kinetics as well as ion transport by diffusion and migration are accounted for, and the model is therefore referred to as a tertiary current density distribution model.
